From: Performance Patch Series
Subject: [PATCH 16/16] Enable LZ4 compression on Arrow data transfer

The BigQuery Storage API supports server-side compression of Arrow
record batches before sending them over gRPC. By default, buffers are
sent uncompressed.

This patch sets ArrowSerializationOptions.BufferCompression to
LZ4_FRAME in the CreateReadSession request. LZ4 frame compression
typically achieves 2-4x compression on columnar data while
decompressing at ~4 GB/s — the CPU cost is negligible compared to
the network savings for large table imports.

This directly reduces the bytes transferred during the data read
phase measured by MeasureFullTableImport, improving throughput for
network-bound scenarios.

---
 csharp/src/BigQueryStatement.cs | 13 ++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/csharp/src/BigQueryStatement.cs b/csharp/src/BigQueryStatement.cs
index 37cde26..402b4be 100644
--- a/csharp/src/BigQueryStatement.cs
+++ b/csharp/src/BigQueryStatement.cs
@@ -739,7 +739,18 @@ namespace AdbcDrivers.BigQuery
             Activity? activity,
             CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
         {
-            ReadSession rs = new ReadSession { Table = table, DataFormat = DataFormat.Arrow };
+            ReadSession rs = new ReadSession
+            {
+                Table = table,
+                DataFormat = DataFormat.Arrow,
+                ReadOptions = new ReadSession.Types.TableReadOptions
+                {
+                    ArrowSerializationOptions = new ArrowSerializationOptions
+                    {
+                        BufferCompression = ArrowSerializationOptions.Types.CompressionCodec.Lz4Frame
+                    }
+                }
+            };
             BigQueryReadClient bigQueryReadClient = clientMgr.ReadClient;
             activity?.AddEvent("create_read_session_started");
             ReadSession rrs = await bigQueryReadClient.CreateReadSessionAsync("projects/" + projectId, rs, maxStreamCount);
